 - Extra server, by this we mean a "complete" package of a web server, application server and database
 - Separate each server into a singular node, we now have 3 web servers, 3 application servers and 3 databases servers.
 - Extra load balancer, we updated our load balancer to a cluster so we it is no longer a SPOF.
 
This architecture distributes the workload of each part of the networking into a separate module.

Benefits:
 - Separation of concerns.
 - Redundancy.
 - High availability.
 - Deployment without server downtime.
 - Reduced SPOF.
 - Higher performance.
 - Easier to scale.

Downsides:
 - More servers = more likely to suffer a hardware failure.
 - Having to sync codebases between servers.
 - Higher latency due to requests having to travel through multiple servers.
 - More complexity.
 - More expensive.
 - We don't have End to End encryption on this particular example.
